<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Haughty" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Haughty,</orth> 1) arrogantly proud, insolent: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 3, 11</bibl> (Qq <emph>proud</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 23</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.174" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.71" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 71</bibl> (F<hi rend="sub">2. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.71" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 71</bibl> 4</hi> <emph>haught</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.267" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 267</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.502" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 502</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.302" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 302</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 49</bibl>.<lb />2) high-spirited, lofty, adventurous: <cit><quote>will scourge with h. arms this hateful name,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 2, 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in this h. great attempt they laboured to plant the rightful heir,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.79" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 79</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>these h. words of hers have battered me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.78" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 78</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>valiant and virtuous, full of h. courage,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 35</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>whose humble means match not his h. mind,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 2, 37</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>